A personal account refers to a central wallet, which is saved by THA for your private key. In a central wallet, there is no loss of wallet that cannot be recovered, and can be verified to retrieve your wallet and allow you to experience more services. Decentralized Wallet The private key wallet is to go to the central wallet, in the central wallet, all user authentication content, such as trading passwords, private keys, mnemonics, etc. are stored in the user\'s mobile phone local, not stored in the centralized server. If the user mistakenly deletes the wallet, forgets to back up the private key or mnemonics, will not be able to retrieve the wallet.
